SBB Train Information System (STIS)
===================================

STIS is a simple Twitter tool that reports delays in the SBB network (www.sbb) to some Twitter accounts.

At the same time it generates a XML document that can be used for other tools or systems.

XML View:
<sbbprosurf station="zue">
	<report>
		<departure>11:22</departure>
		<type>S-Bahn</type>
		<number>19538</number>
		<terminus>&nbsp;Affoltern am Albis</terminus>
		<predicted>11:22</predicted>

		<notes>&nbsp;</notes>
	</report>
	<report>
		<departure>11:25</departure>
		<type>S-Bahn</type>
		<number>18541</number>
		<terminus>&nbsp;Pf&auml;ffikon SZ</terminus>

		<predicted>11:25</predicted>
		<notes>&nbsp;</notes>
	</report>
	<report>
		<departure>11:27</departure>
		<type>S-Bahn</type>
		<number>18240</number>

		<terminus>&nbsp;Effretikon</terminus>
		<predicted>11:27</predicted>
		<notes>&nbsp;</notes>
	</report>
</sbbprosurf>

Data source
===========
The SBB information comes from http://prosurf.sbb.ch/ and is parsed with htmlsql (http://www.jonasjohn.de/lab/htmlsql.htm).
